CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 31, 1946, pg. 10 reads: "American Bridge Tournament Closes In Pittsburgh - Closing Saturday night in Pittsburgh was one of the most successful of all ABA gatherings, which drew some 500 bridge players to Pennsylvania to spend a week vying for honors. Mrs. Doolie Curiel of New York City raised $300 from those attending the tournament for the United Negro College Fund...All photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Doolie Curiel standing behind table with trophies, in Kay Boys Club, for Thirteenth Annual Conference of the American Bridge Association
